ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Circadian Energy Scale: Energy Level Morning
Circadian Energy Scale: Energy Level Evening
Circadian Energy Scale: Energy Level Afternoon
Circadian Energy Scale Energy Total [RAW SCORE]
Circadian Energy Scale Energy Chrono Type [RAW SCORE]

Notes: Higher score indicates higher total energy level (sum of two items)
4 indicates more evening preference; -4 indicate more morning preference; Difference of PM and AM energy level

1=Morning type; 2=Neither type; 3=Evening type; If Chronotype RS less than or equal to -2, then consider morning type. If Chronotype RS greater than or equal to 2 then consider evening type. Others were grouped as neither type.
